  "text": "Found 15 Go source files across kubernetes/kubernetes and etcd-io/etcd that configure, define, or use the etcd DialTimeout parameter. On the consumer side: staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/storagebackend/factory/etcd3.go defines a package-level dialTimeout constant of 20 seconds and passes it to clientv3.Config.DialTimeout when creating the etcd storage backend. staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/preflight/checks.go uses net.DialTimeout for pre-flight etcd connectivity checks. On the provider side: client/v3/config.go defines the DialTimeout field in the Config struct. client/v3/client.go uses cfg.DialTimeout in three locations to create context deadlines for connection establishment. client/v3/lease.go passes cfg.DialTimeout+1s to NewLeaseFromLeaseClient. client/v3/maintenance.go uses cfg.DialTimeout for maintenance connection contexts. client/pkg/transport/transport.go and timeout_transport.go accept dialtimeoutd parameters for HTTP transport creation. server/config/config.go defines PeerDialTimeout() method. server/etcdserver/server.go calls cfg.PeerDialTimeout() for raft HTTP transport setup. server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/transport.go defines DialTimeout field in Transport struct. server/etcdserver/api/rafthttp/util.go uses dialTimeout parameter in NewRoundTripper and newStreamRoundTripper. server/etcdmain/config.go defines ProxyDialTimeoutMs for gRPC proxy configuration. server/etcdmain/etcd.go passes ProxyDialTimeoutMs to transport creation. server/etcdmain/grpc_proxy.go sets DialTimeout: 5*time.Second for gRPC proxy client connections.",
